$ Excel: Review -> Protect -> Protect Sheet

In some versions of Excel, this Menu is *Review -> Changes -> Protect Sheet*.

*Review -> Protect -> Protect Sheet* allows a user to protect certain aspects of a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet:
  • Select → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/locked[locked cells]
  • Select → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/locked[unlocked cells]
  • Format cells
  • Format columns and/or rows
  • Insert columns and/or rows
  • Delete hyperlinks
  • Delete columns/rows
  • Sort
  • Use AutoFilter
  • Use → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Pivot/Table[PivotTable] & PivotChart
  • Edit objects
  • Edit scenarios

sa:

  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/popups-and-dialogs/Format-Cells#xls-format-cells-protection[Protection tab] of the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/popups-and-dialogs/Format-Cells[Format Cells popup].

  The methods → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet/protect-unprotect[`protect` and `unprotect`] of the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet[`worksheet` object].

  The menu → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home/Cells/Format/Protection[Home -> Cells -> Format -> Protection]

  The functionality that is offered in this menu can also be reached via → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Info/Protect-Workbook[File -> Info -> Protect Workbook] -> Protect Current Sheet.
